ce:section.ce:para:
The detection accuracy of the developed ECL aptasensor for CEA in human serum samples was explored with the standard addition method. Since the CEA concentration in normal human serum is less than 5.00 ng/mL, it was necessary to dilute the human serum sample 1000 times in the following experiments. As can be seen from Table 2
                        , the recoveries ranged from 96.0% to 105.5%. Compared with the results determined by enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) used in hospital (Table 3
                        ), the CEA levels determined by the proposed ECL aptasensor had no significant difference, indicating that it could be used for quantification analysis of CEA in human serum samples.
